[{"name":"wrongly","pos":"adverb","content":"<div class=\"entry\" hclass=\"entry\" sum=\"580\" sk=\"wrongly: :0\" htag=\"section\" hlength=\"7\" id=\"wrongly\" idm_id=\"000067818\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"wrongly_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" hclass=\"headword\" random=\"y\" htag=\"h1\" id=\"wrongly_h_1\">wrongly</h1> <span class=\"pos\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"pos\">adverb</span><span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" hclass=\"phons_br\" wd=\"wrongly\" geo=\"br\" htag=\"div\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/w/wro/wrong/wrongly__gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/w/wro/wrong/wrongly__gb_1.ogg\" title=\"wrongly pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ˈrɒŋli/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" geo=\"n_am\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\" wd=\"wrongly\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/w/wro/wrong/wrongly__us_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/w/wro/wrong/wrongly__us_1.ogg\" title=\"wrongly pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ˈrɔːŋli/</span></div></span></div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"senses_multiple\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" sensenum=\"1\" hclass=\"sense\" id=\"wrongly_sng_2\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">in a way that is not right or correct</span></span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">He assumed, wrongly, that she did not care.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">The sentence had been wrongly translated.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">She was wrongly diagnosed as having skin cancer.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\"><span class=\"cl\">Rightly or wrongly</span>, they felt they should have been better informed <span class=\"gloss\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"gloss\">(= I do not know whether they were right to feel this way)</span>.</span></li></ul>          \n</li><li class=\"sense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"wrongly_sng_1\" hclass=\"sense\" sensenum=\"2\"><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">in a way that is not fair or not morally right</span></span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">She was wrongly accused of stealing.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">They knew they had acted wrongly.</span></li></ul><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"which_word\" id=\"wrongly_unbox_1\"><span class=\"box_title\">Which Word? <span class=\"closed\">wrong / wrongly / wrongfully</span></span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"unbox\">wrong / wrongly / wrongfully</span><ul class=\"bullet\"><li class=\"li\">In informal language <span class=\"eb\">wrong</span> can be used as an adverb instead of <span class=\"eb\">wrongly</span>, when it means ‘incorrectly’ and comes after a verb or its object:<ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">My name was spelt wrong.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">I’m afraid you guessed wrong.</span></li></ul><span class=\"eb\">Wrongly</span> is used before a past participle or a <span class=\"ei\">that</span> clause:<ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">My name was wrongly spelt.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">She guessed wrongly that he was a teacher.</span></li></ul></li><li class=\"li\"><span class=\"eb\">Wrongfully</span> is usually used in a formal legal situation with words like <span class=\"ei\">convicted</span>, <span class=\"ei\">dismissed</span> and <span class=\"ei\">imprisoned</span>.</li></ul></span></span></div><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"snippet\" id=\"wrongly_unbox_2\"><span class=\"box_title\">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"eb\">Wrongly</span> is used with these verbs: <ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\" bord=\"n\">accuse</li><li class=\"li\" bord=\"n\">act</li><li class=\"li\" bord=\"n\">advise</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul></span><span class=\"xref_to_full_entry\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/collocations/wrongly\" title=\" definition in Collocations\n \">full entry</a></span></span></span></div>      </li></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/wrongly\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">wrongly</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/wrongly\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">wrongly</span></a> in the Oxford Learner's Dictionary of Academic English</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/wrongly\">wrongly</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["wrongfully adverb","wrong-headed adjective","wrongly adverb","wrongness noun","wrote verb"]},[]]